Important Points:-

1) This contains code for building a dismissing alert message
2) If you want users to be able to close the message, add a span tag to the alert
3) The span tag should contain an onclick attribute with JavaScript code to hide the message after clicking on the cross (x)
4) Use the HTML "&times;" entity to create the cross (x)
5) Wrap alert in a parent div to set its visible width via the width CSS property
6) Create full-width alert message by setting width of parent div to '100%'
7) With Bootstrap, remove left- and right padding by adding the 'px-0' class to the 'container-fluid' class if using a full-width alert
8) Alternatively, add a custom class to the 'container-fluid' div and apply the 'padding: 0' CSS rule to remove Bootstrap left- and right padding
9) Don't use the class name 'alert' because it's a registered Bootstrap class!
10) If you have multiple alerts, use JavaScript to close them without using the onclick attribute on every span tag
